It’s so sad when people start coming up with all sorts of theories about cigarettes. They’ve been here for a long time and there was no outcry, but now they’re dangerous and ICU won’t cope. Let’s face it: how many of those Covid-19 patients are smokers who got sick or died? Give us the numbers. What I see here are nonsmokers dying from government negligence, and incompetent cabinet ministers. What are the numbers of smokers affected by Covid-19, and the difference between harm from booze and tobacco?